9 AS INTRODUCED
10 An Act relating to motor vehicles; defining terms;
authorizing the placing of hidden disability
11 indicator on certain forms of identification;
providing for optional participation; allowing
12 Service Oklahoma to require certain documents;
requiring indicator not specify disability; allowing
13 removal of indicator without penalty; stating
requirements for indicator; describing prohibited
14 uses of the indicator; authorizing the promulgation
of certain rules; providing for codification; and
15 providing an effective date.
16
17
18 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
19 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
20 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 6-131 of Title 47, unless there
21 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
22 A. As used in this section:
23 1. "Hidden disability" means a non-obvious physical,
24 neurological, sensory, cognitive, or developmental condition that
HB2977 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 may affect communication, perception, movement, or behavior during
2 interactions with law enforcement, including, but not limited to:
3 a. autism spectrum disorder,
4 b. deafness or significant hearing impairment,
5 c. speech impairment,
6 d. cognitive or neurological conditions, and
7 e. physical conditions that may limit mobility or motor
8 response.
9 2. "Indicator" means a standardized logo, symbol, or notation
10 approved by Service Oklahoma that signifies the licensee or
11 cardholder has voluntarily elected to disclose the presence of a
12 hidden disability.
13 B. Service Oklahoma shall allow an applicant or licensee to
14 voluntarily elect to have a hidden disability indicator placed on a
15 driver license or state-issued identification card. No person shall
16 be required to disclose a disability or participate in the program
17 as a condition of licensure or identification. Service Oklahoma may
18 require a signed self-attestation or other reasonable documentation
19 as determined by rule, but shall not require disclosure of a
20 specific diagnosis, medical records, or detailed health information.
21 The indicator shall not specify the nature or category of the
22 disability. A licensee or cardholder may request removal of the
23 indicator at any time. Service Oklahoma shall remove the indicator
24 without penalty or explanation upon request.
HB2977 HFLR Page 2
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 C. The indicator shall be discreet and standardized statewide,
2 clearly recognizable by law enforcement, and nonstigmatizing in
3 appearance and language. The indicator shall not include text
4 describing the disability.
5 D. The indicator shall not be stored or searchable as a medical
6 record. The presence of a hidden disability indicator:
7 1. Shall not create probable cause or reasonable suspicion;
8 2. Shall not be used for investigative, enforcement, or
9 profiling purposes; and
10 3. Shall not be disclosed for purposes other than official
11 identification.
12 E. Service Oklahoma is authorized to promulgate rules to
13 effectuate the provisions of this section.
14 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
15
